  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life-Saving Shelter/NFIs to returnee IDP families of FATA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project objective is to provide life-saving shelter and non-food item assistance to returnee IDP families in FATA.Assistance includes distribution of tents for those who have no means of shelter in the return areas; general NFI kits; winterization kits to help protect the vulnerable returnees from coming winter; and tool kits.  17,500 returnee families are targeted with this assistance.

Total requirement:  $94,420,200
Funding to date:  $5,100,000
CERF requested: $2,794,145</narrative>
  </description>
